name: **Inishbee**
description: Inishbee L904-904 Sheet 30 With a flat area at its N end, and 2/3 remnants of houses, camping is possible. Land at the E facing beach at the NE. Very pleasant, good walking, sheep, locally typical mudwalls between fields. Divided into two parts by a massive linking storm beach spit, the S end is vintage Clew Bay walking on a sausage shaped ridge, the views changing all the time. Very beautiful.
